<div id="I_file">&lt;ios&gt; &lt;iostream&gt;</div>
<h1><span class="namespace" title="namespace std">std::</span>make_error_condition (io_errc)<span class="C_ico cpp11warning" title="This page describes a feature introduced by the latest revision of the C++ standard (2011). Older compilers may not support it." alt="This page describes a feature introduced by the latest revision of the C++ standard (2011). Older compilers may not support it."></span></h1>
<div class="C_prototype"><div class="C_SwitchCases">
<div title="C++11">
<pre>error_code make_error_condition (io_errc e);</pre></div>
<div title="C++14" class="on">
<pre>error_code make_error_condition (io_errc e) noexcept;</pre></div>
</div>
</div><div id="I_description">Make error condition</div>
<section id="description">
Creates an <samp><a href="/error_condition">error_condition</a></samp> object from the <samp><a href="/io_errc">io_errc</a></samp> enum value <var>e</var> (of the <a href="/iostream_category">iostream_category</a>).<br>
<br>
It returns the same as<br>
<div class="auto"><table class="snippet"><tr><td class="rownum"><pre><code>&nbsp;</code></pre></td>
<td class="source"><pre><code>error_condition(<var>static_cast</var>&lt;<var>int</var>&gt;(e),iostream_category());</code></pre></td><td class="C_btnholder"></td></tr></table></div>
<br>
<br>
This overload is called by <samp><a href="/error_condition">error_condition</a></samp>'s constructor when passed an argument of type <samp><a href="/io_errc">io_errc</a></samp>.<br>
</section>
<br>
<section id="parameters">
<h3>Parameters</h3>
<dl>
<dt>e</dt>
<dd>An enum value of type <samp><a href="/io_errc">io_errc</a></samp>.</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<br>
<section id="return">
<h3>Return value</h3>
An <samp><a href="/error_condition">error_condition</a></samp> object representing the enum value <var>e</var>.<br>
</section>
<br>
<section id="exceptions">
<h3>Exception safety</h3>
<b>No-throw guarantee:</b> this function never throws exceptions.<br>
</section>
